
[1]bitterly

   BIT'TERLY, adv. With a bitter taste.

   1. In a severe manner; in a manner expressing poignant grief; as, to
   weep bitterly.

   2. In a manner severely reproachful; sharply; severely; angrily; as, to
   censure bitterly.
